<Verbatim PAsource="" >OASIS guitarist Paul "Bonehead" Arthurs </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >shocked fans last night </New>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >by announcing he is quitting the top </Verbatim>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >rock band.
</Verbatim>

<Verbatim PAsource="" >The 34-year-old </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >millionaire </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >musician is thought to have split </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >amicably </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >from the group, </Verbatim>
<New PAsource="" >fronted by brothers Noel and Liam Gallagher.
</New>

<Verbatim PAsource="" >Paul, a founder of Oasis, said in a statement: "I've had a fantastic eight years in one of the best bands ever to come out of Britain and now feel I have come to the stage where I'd like to concentrate on other things. I intend to enjoy watching the band go on to further success."
</Verbatim>

<Verbatim PAsource="" >There are no plans </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >to replace him, a band </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >spokesman said.
</Verbatim>

<New PAsource="" >A showbusiness insider added: "This comes as a great surprise but it won't mean the end of the band. Their fourth album is in the can."


</New>



